[Crim. No. 1394. First Appellate District, Division Two. December 7, 1927.] THE PEOPLE, Respondent, v. FRANK COSTELLO et al., Defendants; WILLIAM RALEIGH, Appellant.

Milton T. U'Ren and U. Edward Manning for Appellant.

U. S. Webb, Attorney-General, and Win. F. Cleary, Deputy Attorney-General, for Bespondent.

*795NOURSE, J.

Upon the authority of People v. Costello, ante, p. 313 [262 Pac. 75], the appeal of the defendant William Raleigh from the judgment and order denying his motion for a new trial is affirmed.

Koford, P. J., and Sturtevant, J., concurred.
